ct then that will probably help him testify: If you=E2=80=99re going to be =
subjected to withering cross-examination=C2=A0about the crimes you did, it =
helps if you believe that you are innocent.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is Lewis right? I think so! But that is, I thi=
nk, the normal state for a scammer.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foo=
tnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none =
