d-color: #ccc;"> be worse</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banks that financed Elon Musk's $44 billio=
n purchase of Twitter are still struggling a year later to contain the dama=
ge to their balance sheets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banks currently expect to take a hit of at=
 least 15%, or roughly $2 billion, when they sell the debt, people familiar=
 with the matter said. That would mean hundreds of millions in losses for t=
hose holding the largest pieces, which include Morgan Stanley, Bank of Amer=
ica, Barclays and MUFG. BNP Paribas, Soci=C3=A9t=C3=A9 G=C3=A9n=C3=A9rale a=
nd Mizuho were also involved.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After holding the debt for a year -- an eterni=
ty in the corporate-finance world -- the banks, which had hoped they could =
sell it by Labor Day, have recently begun preparations to try to unload at =
least some of it, the people said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around the deal=E2=80=99s closing there was ta=
lk of banks getting bids at 50 cents on the dollar, so 85 would be pretty g=
ood? One purpose of installing Linda Yaccarino as the chief executive offic=
er of Twitter (now called X) is that she can have basically normal conversa=
tions with investors as the banks try to sell the debt; investors will say =
things like =E2=80=9Chow=E2=80=99s business?=E2=80=9D and she will say thin=
gs like =E2=80=9Coh good, good, advertisers coming back, really good.=E2=80=
=9D As opposed to sending Elon Musk to those meetings and having him get bo=
red and start trouble. =E2=80=9CHow=E2=80=99s business,=E2=80=9D investors =
would ask, and he=E2=80=99d be like =E2=80=9Cyou know what I=E2=80=99ve dec=
ided that debt isn=E2=80=99t real=E2=80=9D and you=E2=80=99d never get 85 c=
ents on the dollar.</p>
